{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NQ98jz4fzqNqNtpYG3urCH","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have all the information you need. Here's a comprehensive summary of the coinflip `initialize_config` pattern:\n\n## Summary: Coinflip `initialize_config` Pattern\n\n### 1. **Instruction Definition**\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/instructions/initialize_config.rs`\n\n```rust\nuse anchor_lang::prelude::*;\nuse crate::state::CoinflipConfig;\n\n#[derive(Accounts)]\npub struct InitializeConfig<'info> {\n    /// Admin authority who initializes the config.\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub authority: Signer<'info>,\n\n    /// The config PDA (singleton).\n    #[account(\n        init,\n        payer = authority,\n        space = 8 + CoinflipConfig::INIT_SPACE,\n        seeds = [b\"coinflip_config\"],\n        bump,\n    )]\n    pub config: Account<'info, CoinflipConfig>,\n\n    pub system_program: Program<'info, System>,\n}\n\npub fn handler(ctx: Context<InitializeConfig>, treasury: Pubkey) -> Result<()> {\n    let config = &mut ctx.accounts.config;\n    config.authority = ctx.accounts.authority.key();\n    config.treasury = treasury;\n    config.paused = false;\n    config.bump = ctx.bumps.config;\n\n    Ok(())\n}\n```\n\n**Key patterns**:\n- PDA uses seeds `[b\"coinflip_config\"]` (singleton per program)\n- Authority signs and pays for account creation\n- Handler stores authority, treasury address, initial paused state, and bump seed\n- Uses `INIT_SPACE` for space calculation (8 bytes discriminator + struct size)\n\n### 2. **Instruction Dispatch**\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/lib.rs` (lines 15-17)\n\n```rust\n#[program]\npub mod coinflip {\n    use super::*;\n\n    pub fn initialize_config(ctx: Context<InitializeConfig>, treasury: Pubkey) -> Result<()> {\n        instructions::initialize_config::handler(ctx, treasury)\n    }\n    // ... other instructions\n}\n```\n\n### 3. **Config State Struct**\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/state.rs` (lines 4-17)\n\n```rust\n/// Global configuration for the coinflip program.\n/// PDA seeds: [b\"coinflip_config\"]\n#[account]\n#[derive(InitSpace)]\npub struct CoinflipConfig {\n    /// Admin authority (can update config).\n    pub authority: Pubkey,\n    /// Fee destination wallet.\n    pub treasury: Pubkey,\n    /// Whether the game is paused (rejects new matches).\n    pub paused: bool,\n    /// Bump seed for PDA derivation.\n    pub bump: u8,\n}\n```\n\n### 4. **Bankrun Test**\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/tests/coinflip.ts` (lines 359-372)\n\n```typescript\ndescribe(\"initialize_config\", () => {\n  it(\"creates config with treasury and paused=false\", async () => {\n    const t = await createTestContext();\n    await initConfig(t);\n\n    const config = await t.creatorProgram.account.coinflipConfig.fetch(\n      t.configPda\n    );\n    expect(config.authority.toBase58()).to.equal(t.creator.toBase58());\n    expect(config.treasury.toBase58()).to.equal(\n      t.treasury.publicKey.toBase58()\n    );\n    expect(config.paused).to.equal(false);\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Test helper** (lines 194-203):\n```typescript\nasync function initConfig(t: TestContext) {\n  await t.creatorProgram.methods\n    .initializeConfig(t.treasury.publicKey)\n    .accounts({\n      authority: t.creator,\n      config: t.configPda,\n      systemProgram: SystemProgram.programId,\n    })\n    .rpc();\n}\n```\n\n**PDA derivation helper** (lines 68-74):\n```typescript\nfunction getConfigPda(): PublicKey {\n  const [pda] = PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    [Buffer.from(\"coinflip_config\")],\n    PROGRAM_ID\n  );\n  return pda;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Replication Checklist for `lordofrngs`\n\nTo replicate this for lordofrngs:\n1. Create `instructions/initialize_config.rs` with same `#[derive(Accounts)]` pattern\n2. Define `LordofrngsConfig` struct in `state.rs` with similar fields (authority, treasury, paused, bump)\n3. Add dispatch in `lib.rs` → `instructions::initialize_config::handler(ctx, treasury)`\n4. Update PDA seed to `[b\"lordofrngs_config\"]` instead of `[b\"coinflip_config\"]`\n5. Write test in `solana/tests/` following the same bankrun pattern with `getConfigPda()` helper\n\nAll files are ready for reference!"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a1392fa (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 43327\ntool_uses: 6\nduration_ms: 15406</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"dce9785d-7f4b-4c3e-bdf0-c7aac93dbc9e","uuid":"3a1e724b-d56c-4cea-8add-2bfb4167e68a","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read the following files and return their full contents. I need to understand the coinflip `initialize_config` instruction pattern to replicate it for lordofrngs:\n\n1. `sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/instructions/initialize_config.rs`\n2. `sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/lib.rs` (just the instruction dispatch section)\n3. `sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/state.rs` (just the config struct)\n\nAlso check if there are existing bankrun tests for coinflip's initialize_config:\n4. Look for test files in `sources/rng-utopia/solana/tests/` that test initialize_config for coinflip\n\nReturn the full file contents for all files found.","agentId":"a1392fa","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have all the information you need. Here's a comprehensive summary of the coinflip `initialize_config` pattern:\n\n## Summary: Coinflip `initialize_config` Pattern\n\n### 1. **Instruction Definition**\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/instructions/initialize_config.rs`\n\n```rust\nuse anchor_lang::prelude::*;\nuse crate::state::CoinflipConfig;\n\n#[derive(Accounts)]\npub struct InitializeConfig<'info> {